@RudbeckiaSun I can understand that. Good sibling for telling you what to say as well. I'm so glad my mother never qualified, I can only imagine the horror of her telling people the wrong thing because of her limited views.
Fun fact: this is why I don't bother to ask the doc for meds anymore because I am still convinced I'm not allowed them. Even though, y'know, pain everywhere. So that's fun too.

She is thank fuck, not a doctor and did not qualify as one, but she still believes mental health isn't a thing that needs treating, doesn't believe in pain meds, believes you can't have more than one health condition at a time, and doesn't believe I'm autistic/have Adhd/EDS/etc.

Stared*. Anyway, after that I felt fucking fantastic, and was super pissed that my mother wouldn't let me take any sort of medication because it was real fucking bad, she said they couldn't possibly be that bad, and I learnt she was not to be trusted with med talk.

That set off all the dysphoria in the goddamn world, I tell you. Period started at school once, went to the nurse asking to be sent home because I didn't know painkillers were an option. She stated at me funny, gave me a nurofen and told me to go back to class.

11. And my mother, training to be a doctor, would not let me take any painkillers, to the point where I would scavenge the house desperately trying to find any expired medication we might have in the hope it helped. She'd rather I stayed off school sick. https://t.co/mp5DX7hf8g

Because at the end of the day, I'm not who this person has constructed in their head. That isn't me, and people who know me know that. I am not responsible for the distorted abusive version of me they created in their head to make themselves feel better.

I know myself. I know I tried hard to settle things on good terms, and I'm not in control of the reactionary bullshit that came my way afterwards. I word things as well as I can do to avoid misconstrued meanings and it's not my fault they chose to read into what they wanted to.

Honestly though, people will call you all manner of names in the hope it gets you to shut up. Rather than listen and agree to part ways like adults, they'd rather continue to flout authority and be openly ableist and aggressive to anyone who has any contrasting opinion to them.

Programmed to look good when viewed from the front, the reverse was a sad degrading mess of cracks and quick-fixes, held together by spit and luck.

The closer Wren crept to the edges of the enclosure -  shored up bulkheads covered with touch-reactive vines and mycological oddities - the more the glitches in the holojections fluttered and sparked.

The closer Wren got to them, the more obvious it became that the shine of the patina was a mere fantasy, partially holojected, slowly decaying down into a dusting of fake precipitation upon the foliage below.

The sheen of forgotten grandeur lingered here and there in the decadent architecture: in the sculptural ivory towers Wren had once wondered at as a youngling, meandering between them in awe at their silent undulations against the backdrop of black space.

The Gardens of Restraint at the back of this particular Estate was perhaps not the best example the Empire had to offer, given the lack of upkeep and guard rotation; probably due to its distance from the usual shipping lanes and lack of favour with the Empress herself.

Relationships to people - whether natural, digital, or technologically advanced -were basic at best, and the governess AI had reprimanded them for their naivety and easy trusting nature a number of times. 

Wren had only been ten when they learned what an Imprint truly was.

Carefully bred and controlled in an environment away from the other Empress-elect potentials, and kept away from the tribulations and political landscape of the entire known universe had left Wren in a very disadvantageous state when it came to many things.

The Empress Below, their genetic donor, and matriarchal figure to the Edge of the Universe and Beyond, had never been particularly good at covering up her own messes and miscalculations. Wren had been one of them.

I absolutely need to get back on the piano too, I realised that whilst I have lost a lot of flexibility when it comes to playing, I can still weave a tune around pretty well enough to post every so often. And we finally, finally have decent recording equipment!

Also, hey! I wrote something that challenges me. And a few people have read it and provided feedback which I am grateful for. Maybe I could submit it places this year if it is finished soon. That sounds like a nice thing to maybe do this year.
I regret and grieve what could have been, what could have been read, or seen, or experienced, but those spheres of possibility are lost to me now; better sooner rather than later.

Our house is small but mighty, and in the face of the darkness, we thrive and prevail and scream "fuck you!" in joyous abandon. I am too old to set stock in things which do not please me, or people who sabotage for fun.

I found myself a new job where they value me a little more, got myself into the intersectional group we have and started to make some damn changes and unsettled the status quo. Hell, I wrote more this year than I have since I was 18. Found some new hobbies! Picked up old ones.

I have lost friends the last year, lost people I thought were friends, probably made some people apathetic, annoyed, and irritated with my existence. But I have kept friends, found new ones, found new family, and I continue to exist, and thrive, and my spite breezes on.

I was also excited to see a young russian composer at the helm bc so often the same old music jobs go to the same old type of people, and I love seeing people do new things with music, and get recognised for it. And the music blends so well with the already existing music for TW.
@GV_Pearce yeeeeeep. all in your head, clearly doesn't exist long term, we know nothing, and we don't wanna research it either. :/

The themes we got were heartwrenchingly human, and slide together in a beautiful cacophony of emotion and made me listen to them for hours on end, just...vibing. enjoying the interplay and some of the atonal parts which just added to the tension and the build-up in the story.

i've listened to more of this new composer's work and I'm just underwhelmed. I don't like banality in music, and that's on me, but I sort of expected more, especially when being handed the reigns by the absolute gods of music we were lucky to have for s1.

i'm one of those weird people who asks others what the music was like in a film at the cinema, and get very confused looks afterwards, because the music to me is as integral as the cinematography, or the acting. and to not pay attention to it seems wrong and erasery.

i'm aware I'm being harsh. It's not like I have the professional cred to back any of this up. my credentials are just that I was trained as a concert pianist when younger and wasn't allowed to progress further professionally. but goddamn, I know good music when I hear it.

of the whole witcher netflix shebang. the music felt like a proper meld of sound design and music all in one, and this sounds like a box-ticking exercise done the night before with no real enjoyment or love, or even a spark of individual joy.

It should be able to stand on its own and evolve with the story, and I fear that if s2's music is much like the song that's dropped on spotify now, it's going to be going backwards, and making the music just....feel like an afterthought, instead of being one of the best parts

plus, y'know, widely used in europe, so perfect for witcher. this new song just sounds so cookie-cutter fantasy soundtrack, I'm bored. I shouldn't be bored when listening to this. The music is there to emphasize and really lift the action.

The use of hurdy-hurdy was absolutely key as well - it's a beautiful instrument and so underused, and it fits perfectly in the soundscape for the witcher. It's not exactly high-brow-sounding, but it's so unbelievably human.

one of the joyous parts of the s1 soundtrack was how raw it sounded. it didn't hold to the traditional semitone/full-tone scale and just bled across the music in a beautiful scream - in the violin solos for example. The percussive elements were there too.

definitely this is veering off into salty territory though so.  hmm. And obviously only based off 5 to 10 minutes of music (track on spotify, some trailer stuff, promos).

@stimmyskye I am glad the meds help! And yeah, rehearsing it mentally helps so much too! I have to be careful not to stretch my fingers too much because dislocations/tendon pain as well. Ahh I love hearing about your violin journey.
@stimmyskye I still sit and 'play piano' in the air, or on my knees to stim and it is so much fun. Especially if you do it whilst listening to music and make the movements match up with the music.
@stimmyskye Obviously not too much because fingers can be tricky little hypermobile bastards sometimes. But a little bit as a stimming technique was my favourite thing to do when bored.

@stimmyskye Oh and if you can do it, if you have spoons when not playing violin, I always found that practising the fingerings movements in the air, or on my arm, helped cement the motion a little. So when you use the instrument you have more muscle memory and it helps to ease muscles in.

@stimmyskye And yeah, do the exercises you at least find a little joy in. And then add a little bit of the ones you don't, but not too much. Only a little bit so you can remain happy at the fun ones. It's about enjoyment and slowing building up strength

@stimmyskye Oh I miss doing arpeggios on the violin! So beautiful. And there is a mathematical feel to the positioning as well, so very good for stimming!
I wish I still had my electric violin to practise on! Might have to ask my brother to steal it from the parents.
@stimmyskye It is such a slog doing scales and bits that are so so boring, but it is worth it. You've improved so much in the time you've been playing!

@stimmyskye A little bit every day, and you'll notice your improvements, I promise. I always used to get my students to go through exercises at the beginning of a lesson and then we'd pick a fun song they liked to then use those skills so they wanted to practice more.

Anyway, this is brought to you by major anxiety over Neff's CT scan tomorrow morning, the fact that my anxiety is sky high, and the fact that the adhd team haven't answered my emails so fuck knows if i'm ever allowed medication that works for me. (and it does!)

Then /i/ feel the need to apologise and appease and keep the peace for some fucken reason. I dunno. Placate and depersonalise myself. Mask and stay quiet. But I can't because I cannot mask worth two shits these days.

Worst part is: I still want to be friends with them because I'm a fucking pushover. I'm not badass or cool or disaffected or whatever, I'm just genuinely upset when people misconstrue shit, don't listen to what I say, and then act like it's my fault they jumped the gun.
@GizzarkHenry <3

Also, autistic, so. Y'know. I ask and hope in good faith people will tell me. And sometimes they do! And it's good! I can then amend stuff and not be an ass unintentionally!

But when they say they will, and then won't and then vague about it, that's the bit that upsets me.

I ask every so often for people to tell me honestly if stuff i'm doing is annoying because if I spent all day analysing cues and what ifs I'd honestly never speak to anyone again. My brain tells me everything I do is annoying, or burdensome, I cannot be trusted to know.

I curate myself and try not to get annoying when I get excited because I know I am very much too much for some people.

You know the feeling when you think you found your people? And then, no, you didn't and everyone hates you, and doesn't tell you, even after you've asked.

Having a moment of argh where I'm trying to make myself not care about being ignored, but also simultaneously being unable to not care. Trying to not believe that it is me that sucks here, because goddammit I try really fucking hard, and I try not to step on toes and upset people

But yeah, anyway, before I get distracted by shark teeth again. No big plot. I have to believe this is the case or else I will be distressed unduly and I've already had to take days off work to try and feel this out in a way that I can cope.
(for me I hasten to add. I have nothing against other people using hand wave magic to explain things! I just love grinding down the little details until it feels it could work).

Part of me is like well, yes, I wrote that spin because I adore mixing real world science with the potential of fantasy applications, I love writing about chimerical beings and mutations in fiction. It's nice to have something that isn't hand waving magic this is how it works.

Because yeah, there is a level of hurt that happens when you create something and you wanna share it but then the level of response is small. You can't help a lot of the factors involved in that except some small ones. And often those factors feel like some sort of evil plot.

I can only keep throwing it out there and seeing if it resonates with people. Hilariously the cannibal one did decently! Maybe people like less of the potential science behind procedures in the story? Is it less interesting or fun? I don't know. It would be good to know.

And like. I'm sad my stuff never gets as much of a response when spinning. I should expect that as someone who does not actively produce prose I can share. I have no one to blame but my inability to churn words out (thanks trauma, you have a lot to answer for quite honestly).

But also I'm goddamn proud of that spin I did as to why and how witchers could theoretically regrow teeth when certain gene expressions are activated, and what the cut off points in age might be when administering the mutagenic compounds as to how likely it would work.
Now I'm sat here like goddammit Rae. That was so obvious, what the hell?! You fool. You ludicrous excuse for a pseudoscientist.

I wish my brain didn't jump logical steps as well. It got pointed out that the reasonable thing would have been to enact X. Never freaking occurred to me! Brain didn't even realise that was a valid action. Like when I close the fridge but didn't realise I have to remove hands 1st

But then it removes me from some people I enjoy talking to regularly. And that's too big of a thing to lose the chance of, even though I know right now I am probably not going to receive that passive affirmation of 'hey it' s chill you're here'

It is frustrating knowing I have to sit on my hands and not say or do anything. The easiest way to do this would be to ask for a temporary removal of me for a week because then I /know/ I'm not going to sit here constantly refreshing and analysing every single thing.

Fixing and sorting it is out of my hands, unless I directly ask /everyone/ vaguely involved how we stand. Which is not helpful, when you know people probably want space. But one of these things that I think is exacerbated by neurodivergence is I cannot handle that wait.

Even though the brain spiral is saying 'look this is exactly the same situation you thought you were in the right then and  you're definitely wrong now so clearly you deserve this perceived grievance'. Fuck you, brain. I think the problem is, I need it to be fixed and sorted.

I am currently ignoring the Thing that happened 9 (jesus) years ago because honestly I still believe in standing up against bigotry and if it's just me who has to suffer I would rather that, even though it has taken years to confront that specific trauma.

I have to have some sort of belief in the fact that i do not think any of these people would do that. I like them. Prior to shit, I thought they were at least amiable towards me. Now the brain spiral is telling me everyone hates me, which s a concept is laughable.

Brain is pulling the 'there is a conspiracy and now everyone is talking shit about you and not responding on purpose' and like. No, brain, logically that is stupid and ridiculous, I know that is RSD talking but also goddamn it what if it is true because of the times where it was?
